{
  "text": "To create a new generation of lambs, values for r A (used in equation (2.3)) and r E (used in equation (2.6)) for each new lamb were calculated. The additive genetic component (or breeding value) for each offspring is given by i.e. it is simply the mean of the parental values plus a Mendelian sampling term [CITATION_1] . The environmental component is as given by equation (2.2).",
